
# Basic json

1. data types: 
	- string, number, boolean, 
	- arrays
		- can mix data types
		- e.g. [65, "toast", true, 21, null, 100]
	- objects
		- {
			"firstName" : "Peter",
			"lastName" : "Collins",
			"employed" : true
		  }
	-nesting

2. example
2.1
{
	"song":
	{
		"title": "JSON Lullaby",
		"artist": "The Instructors",
		"musicians": 
			["Jen Trainer", "John Teacher"]
	}
}

2.2
[
	{
		"header": "File",
		"items": [
			{"id": "Open", "label": "Open"},
	 	{"id": "New", "label": "New"},
	 	{"id": "Close", "label": "Close"}
	 ]
	},
	{
		"header": "View",
		"items": [
			{"id": "ZoomIn", "label": "Zoom In"},
			{"id": "ZoomOut", "label": "Zoom Out"},
			{"id": "OriginalView", "label": "Original View"}
		]
	}
]

2.3
{
   "Monday": {
      "description": "sunny",
      "maxTemp": 22,
      "minTemp": 20,
      "windSpeed": 12,
      "danger": false
   }
}

